components.name: Action Bar
components.description: Action Bars contain primary and secondary actions related to a page or task.

components.name: Segmented Control
components.description: Switch between alternate view of the same content.

components.name: Delete Button
components.description: Reserved for destructive actions that involve the removal of data.

components.name: Tertiary Button
components.description: Tertiary Buttons have the lowest emphasis. Use for less important actions that the user may not often be looking to do.

components.name: Secondary Button
components.description: Secondary Buttons have a medium level of emphasis. Use them for non-critical actions.

components.name: Primary Button
components.description: Primary Buttons are high emphasis. Use once per screen to draw attention to the highest priority action.

components.name: Side Panel
components.description: Side Panels are containers that anchor to the left or right side of the screen.

components.name: Tabs
components.description: Allows the user to alternate between related views while remaining in the same context.

components.name: Expandable Container
components.description: Expandable Container hides and shows information to create a focused experience for our users.

components.name: Table
components.description: Tables are an efficient way of displaying sets of repeating data with the same structure.

components.name: Table / Row
components.description: Tables are an efficient way of displaying sets of repeating data with the same structure.

components.name: Table / Column
components.description: Tables are an efficient way of displaying sets of repeating data with the same structure.

components.name: Card
components.description: A Card is a preview that serves as an entry point to more detailed information.

components.name: Information Highlight (Preview)
components.description: Information Highlights call out important information on a page or a section of a page that the user should be aware of.

components.name: Status Indicators
components.description: Status Indicators help the user quickly identify the status of a task, action, or page element.

components.name: Skeleton
components.description: A low-fidelity visual placeholder that represents the loading of interface elements before they have displayed on the page

components.name: Pill
components.description: Pills are static or interactive elements that allow users to input, filter, or label information.

components.name: Loading Sparkle
components.description: Loading Sparkles inform users that an AI operation is in progress.

components.name: Loading Dots
components.description: Loading Dots inform users that content is being loaded.

components.name: Count Badge
components.description: Displays an amount, with styling.

components.name: Banner
components.description: Banners surface important information and feedback to the user about a task, action, or state.

components.name: Avatar
components.description: Represents a person's profile.

components.name: Switch
components.description: Switch is a selection control that is used to switch between two potential states.

components.name: Color Picker
components.description: Color Input lets a user specify a color by entering a hexadecimal value into a text field.

components.name: Color Preview
components.description: Color Input lets a user specify a color by entering a hexadecimal value into a text field.

components.name: Color Input
components.description: Color Input lets a user specify a color by entering a hexadecimal value into a text field.

components.name: Form Field
components.description: Form Field is a wrapper for input components to make them accessible for forms.

components.name: Search Form
components.description: Input for search

components.name: Text Area
components.description: Text Areas allow users to enter and edit multiple lines of text.

components.name: MultiSelect Input
components.description: Select allows users to choose one option from a list of items in a Menu.

components.name: Select/Input
components.description: Select allows users to choose one option from a list of items in a Menu.

components.name: Radio/Group
components.description: Radio Buttons allow a user to select one value from a predefined list of 7 or fewer options.

components.name: Radio/Single
components.description: Radio Buttons allow a user to select one value from a predefined list of 7 or fewer options.

components.name: Checkbox/Group
components.description: Checkboxes allow a user to select zero, one, or multiple values from a predefined list of 7 or less options.

components.name: Checkbox/Single
components.description: Checkboxes allow a user to select zero, one, or multiple values from a predefined list of 7 or less options.

components.name: Pagination
components.description: Pagination allows users to navigate through large amounts of content or data divided across multiple pages while making it clear that more pages exist.

components.name: Breadcrumbs
components.description: Breadcrumbs are a secondary form of navigation that allow users to keep track and maintain awareness of their location as they move through different pages, folders, or files.

components.name: Tooltip
components.description: Tooltips reveal contextual information about an element on hover.

components.name: Toast
components.description: Toasts contain updates or messages about the status of an application’s process.

components.name: Menu
components.description: Menus display a list of up to 15 options when launched by an action or UI element like an icon or button.

components.name: Dialog
components.description: Dialogs are a type of interactive pop-up that only contains informative content. Dialogs does not have an overlay behind it.

components.name: Modal
components.description: Modals are a type of interactive pop-up that can contain input fields or informative content. Modals will have an overlay behind it.
